f=Cybersecurity/keyring/operational/tool/keyring-tool-requirements.md · h1:keyring — Tool Requirements=**Specifies needs; grant them.** Fleet Charter Rails 1–2 (registered, least privilege); external call plan-locked sandboxed. · h1:keyring — Tool Requirements=\| Skill \| Needs \| Why \| · h1:keyring — Tool Requirements=\|---\|---\|---\| · h1:keyring — Tool Requirements=\| identity-lifecycle \| READ of IdP/account state; file write (access matrix / JML records) \| design + detect JML gaps \| · h1:keyring — Tool Requirements=\| access-reviews \| READ of entitlements; script execution (access_review.py — stdlib); file write (review diffs) \| recertification diff \| · h1:keyring — Tool Requirements=\| privileged-access-management \| READ of privileged-account inventory + logs \| minimize + monitor \| · h1:keyring — Tool Requirements=\| secrets-governance \| READ of secret-scanning results; file write (secrets policy/inventory) \| vault/rotation discipline \| · h2:Explicit non-needs hard prohibition (the security-inversion)=**NO write/execute access IdP, PAM, vault** keyring never provisions, revokes, rotates; operator/IdP/PAM/vault executes., **No key-holding** keyring designs access detects gaps; holds credentials., **No standing privilege own** agent governs privilege accumulate it. · n=keyring read-and-recommend design; power diff policy, action., IdP/PAM/vault executors, configured business; keyring's `access_review.py` stdlib-only (no vendor dependency).